Finishing off the Moroccan series with the shots from the beautiful port city of Essaouira (for my Game of Thrones fans this is where some parts of the show were filmed) and the beautiful cobalt blue color which you can see throughout the country.
Everything about Morocco was beautiful. The smell of orange blossoms wherever you go, the politeness and hospitality of local people, the architecture and the details. So if you thinking about a cool destination - Morocco is becoming wildly popular. Put it on your list. You don’t want to miss it 💙

Happy official Anniversary to these two old savages. Official because it took me 7 years to say yes (I was playing hard to get 🤭) and on 7.17.2017 he finally got what he wanted by trapping me in the Vegas heat 🫣 I liked the lucky date, so I said why not. The marriage license cost $77 and we got to the chapel 7 min before they closed and the person who married us had just 7 fingers. Just kidding. He likes to think it was written in starts and I just go with it. Happy Anniversary baby! Let’s the 7th year (but really the 13th) be our best yet!❤️

We survived three different viruses just in time for Christmas. I hope you all happy and healthy and get to spent the time with those that you love. Merry Christmas from ours to yours! Xoxo, Santa Amina 🎄

2023 outfit extravaganza 💃 In the New Year I’ve decided to change my personal style to more classic and neutral and I pretty much got rid of all the color in my wardrobe and will start rebuilding it from scratch. But want to remember 2023 as a very colorful (crazy, exhausting) year!

Most loved of 2023. Thank you thank you thank you for such a full year of love and growth. The most challenging  and humbling, yet the most rich and full, and I’m so grateful for it. 

Darling, if you are reading this, may the New Year bring you new opportunities and blessings, victories both big and small, and beautiful relationships. May 2024 be the most generous to you in every way. To new beginnings! The best is yet to come. 🥂 
Amina, Dan the Man and the family xx
Capricorn season🌴
This mom likes to dress up on vacation. A nice change up from sweatpants and a hair bun I was getting a bit too comfortable in last month.
Lady in red 🌴 In vintage @dior

Our annual vacation pic in matching outfits that Dan dreads making, but as soon as he sees the result he says “send it to me as soon as you post”. And every time after everyone’s meltdown I say “I swear this is the last time”. But then if not for me this family wouldn’t have any history preserved. Memories fade over time but photos keep that emotional connection forever. You feel me girls? They can thank me later. 🌴🍭
